<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-83-0736 </DOCNO><TEXT>It is claimed that the trade union movement has never been immune frompolitical conflicts or manipulation. On a world level, the internationalaffiliation of the free trade unions is constantly challenged by theSoviet bloc and its agents. The International Miners Organization, supportedby the USSR and led by Arthur Scargill may constitute a dangerous threatto economic stability and to democratic governments of the West. ArthurScargill's political career is recounted, including his promotion ofthe 1972 and 1984 UK miners' strikes and his involvement with the SovietUnion.</TEXT></DOC>